params.name: data.kms_key_name
params.description: The name of the encryption key that is stored in Google Cloud KMS.

params.name: data.kms_key_service_account
params.description: The service account being used for the encryption request for the given KMS key. If absent, the Compute Engine default service account is used.

params.name: data.raw_key
params.description: Specifies a 256-bit customer-supplied encryption key, encoded in RFC 4648 base64 to either encrypt or decrypt this resource.

params.name: data.sha256
params.description: [Output only] The RFC 4648 base64 encoded SHA-256 hash of the customer-supplied encryption key that protects this resource.
